<p class="">The hon. Member for North Paddington suggests that the reason under 60 Divisions are shown between November and Whitsun for himself, <span id="2460" class="column-number" data-column-number="2460"></span> the hon. Member for East Aberdeen, and the right hon. Member for Epping, is that of the 154 possible Divisions, on 96 occasions they were unable to support the Government. I wonder why it is that they can still—</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
